<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 02 at 8:30AM EST  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...LOCALLY DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
An area of dense fog extending from the Lake Erie shoreline and
the immediate Buffalo metropolitan area to the airport will
continue to reduce the visibility in many areas to under a quarter
mile at times.
While the fog is expected to thin and dissipate as we push past 10
AM...motorists will need to be vigilant for rapid changes in
visibility and should exercise extra caution when traveling
through the area.
When driving through fog...slow down and be sure to leave plenty
of distance ahead of you.</description>
